21/12/2006
BELGRADE, Serbia -- Macedonian Defence Minister Lazar Elenkovski visited Belgrade on Wednesday (December 20th), launching a regional tour that includes stops in Serbia, Montenegro and Bosnia and Herzegovina. His talks with Serbian counterpart Zoran Stankovic focused on issues related to bilateral ties and Kosovo. Elenkovski stressed Macedonia's firm support for Serbia's NATO integration process. He and Stankovic agreed on future joint training of their countries' armed forces and co-operation in terms of international military missions abroad. (Vecer - 21/12/06; A1 TV, Telma TV, Beta - 20/12/06)
